# TypeScript

> JavaScript with static type definitions for better tooling, documentation, and error prevention.

---

## Overview

TypeScript is a typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript:
- **Static Types**: Catch errors at compile time, not runtime
- **IDE Support**: Autocomplete, refactoring, go-to-definition
- **Documentation**: Types serve as inline documentation
- **Gradual Adoption**: Can be added incrementally to JS projects
- **Modern Features**: ES6+ features with type safety

---

## Why TypeScript

| Benefit | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Error Prevention | Catch bugs before they ship |
| Better DX | Autocomplete and refactoring |
| Self-Documenting | Types explain intent |
| Safer Refactoring | Compiler catches breaking changes |
| Industry Standard | Required for most frontend jobs |

