## Interfaces & Types

### Interfaces

```typescript
// Object shape
interface User {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  email: string;
  age?: number; // Optional
  readonly createdAt: Date; // Cannot be modified
}

// Extending interfaces
interface Admin extends User {
  permissions: string[];
}

// Index signatures
interface Dictionary {
  [key: string]: string;
}

// Function signature
interface SearchFunction {
  (query: string, limit?: number): Promise<Result[]>;
}
```

### Type Aliases

```typescript
// Type alias
type ID = string | number;
type Status = "pending" | "active" | "archived";

// Object type
type Point = {
  x: number;
  y: number;
};

// Union type
type Result = Success | Failure;

// Intersection type
type AdminUser = User & { permissions: string[] };

// Template literal types
type EventName = `on${Capitalize<string>}`;
type HTTPMethod = "GET" | "POST" | "PUT" | "DELETE";
```

### Interface vs Type

```typescript
// Interfaces can be extended/merged
interface Window {
  customProperty: string;
}

// Types cannot be re-opened
// type Window = { ... } // Error if already defined

// Use interfaces for objects that might be extended
// Use types for unions, primitives, tuples
```

